ntion": "slincR", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9522047638893127, "span": {"begin": 457, "end": 463}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "long", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.8988515138626099, "span": {"begin": 469, "end": 473}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "long non-coding RNA", "obj": "RNA", "prob": 0.7364652752876282, "span": {"begin": 469, "end": 488}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "lncRNA", "obj": "RNA", "prob": 0.7992675304412842, "span": {"begin": 490, "end": 496}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:7955"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "zebrafish", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9289814829826355, "span": {"begin": 530, "end": 539}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:7955"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "zebrafish", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9665635824203491, "span": {"begin": 573, "end": 582}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:81892"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "slincR", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.99149090051651, "span": {"begin": 604, "end": 610}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:196"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Ahr", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9930757284164429, "span": {"begin": 642, "end": 645}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6662"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "sox9b", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9961263537406921, "span": {"begin": 661, "end": 666}}], "text": "Sox9b (one of two paralogs of the sox9 gene in zebrafish) is one of the most reduced transcripts in the jaw upon TCDD exposure in zebrafish (Xiong et al., 2008).     One question that remained unanswered was the possible mechanisms by which Ahr was regulating sox9b expression, given that even though there are eight putative AHREs near the sox9b promoter, its repression in zebrafish does not occur immediately after TCDD exposure (Xiong et al. 2008).     slincR is a long non-coding RNA (lncRNA) that was recently discovered in zebrafish. Multiple lines of evidence from zebrafish experiments point to slincR being the intermediate between Ahr activation and sox9b repression (Garcia et al., 2017; Garcia et al., 2018).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:46:55 +0000 2026"}